    <!-- AFTER THE SHOW -->
    <div class="page">
        <h2>After the Show: Follow-Up Strategy</h2>

        <p>The show is over, but your work isn't done. Here's how to maximize your investment of time.</p>

        <h3><span class="section-number">1</span>Organize Your Information (Day 1)</h3>

        <p>Within 24 hours of the show:</p>
        <ul class="standard-list">
            <li>Organize all business cards, brochures, and notes by preference</li>
            <li>Upload all photos to a dedicated folder</li>
            <li>Create a comparison spreadsheet of your top choices</li>
            <li>Review pricing and note any discrepancies</li>
        </ul>

        <h3><span class="section-number">2</span>The 48-Hour Window</h3>

        <p>Contact your top 2-3 dealers within 48 hours. This keeps you fresh in their minds and maintains negotiating momentum. Email template:</p>

        <div class="intro-box">
            <p><em>Subject: Following up on [Boat Model] from [Show Name]</em></p>
            <p><em>Hi [Salesperson Name],</em></p>
            <p><em>Thank you for your time at [Show Name] this week. I'm very interested in the [Model] we discussed. I'm comparing it with [Competitor Model] and expect to make a decision within [timeframe].</em></p>
            <p><em>Can you confirm the out-the-door pricing we discussed was $[amount] including [list everything]?</em></p>
            <p><em>Also, can you provide [specific question]?</em></p>
            <p><em>Best regards,<br>[Your Name]<br>[Phone]</em></p>
        </div>

        <h3><span class="section-number">3</span>Additional Research</h3>

        <ul class="standard-list">
            <li><strong>Owner forums:</strong> Search for model-specific forums to hear from actual owners</li>
            <li><strong>YouTube reviews:</strong> Watch independent reviews, not manufacturer videos</li>
            <li><strong>Survey results:</strong> Check NADA guides or J.D. Power ratings</li>
            <li><strong>Insurance quotes:</strong> Get actual quotes for each model you're considering</li>
            <li><strong>Maintenance costs:</strong> Research typical annual maintenance expenses</li>
        </ul>

        <h3><span class="section-number">4</span>The Counter-Offer Strategy</h3>

        <p>If you're serious about buying, now is the time to negotiate hard. After the show rush, dealers have clearer pictures of what sold and what didn't.</p>

        <p>Email your top choice with:</p>

        <div class="intro-box">
            <p><em>"I'm ready to purchase [Model] this week if we can agree on terms. My budget is $[X], which is $[amount] below your quote. Can you meet this price? If so, I'll come in to finalize paperwork."</em></p>
        </div>

        <div class="page-footer">
            The Boat Pro Newsletter | support@theboatpro.com | Page 15
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- AFTER THE SHOW CONTINUED -->
    <div class="page">
        <h2>After the Show: Continued</h2>

        <h3><span class="section-number">5</span>The Waiting Game</h3>

        <p>If you're not in a rush, patience pays off. Many dealers will contact you 2-4 weeks after the show with better offers if boats haven't sold.</p>

        <h3><span class="section-number">6</span>Pre-Purchase Actions</h3>

        <p>Before finalizing any purchase:</p>

        <ul class="checklist">
            <li>Get pre-purchase survey on used boats (hire certified marine surveyor)</li>
            <li>Arrange for sea trial (for used boats)</li>
            <li>Verify all equipment is included and functional</li>
            <li>Confirm delivery date and location</li>
            <li>Get written warranty information</li>
            <li>Verify dealer service department capabilities</li>
            <li>Finalize insurance coverage</li>
            <li>Secure slip or storage space</li>
            <li>Schedule captain training if needed</li>
        </ul>

        <h3><span class="section-number">7</span>Delivery Day Inspection</h3>

        <p>When your boat is delivered, inspect it thoroughly before signing acceptance. Bring this checklist:</p>

        <ul class="checklist">
            <li>Verify model and serial numbers match contract</li>
            <li>Check for any damage during transport</li>
            <li>Test all electronics and systems</li>
            <li>Verify all promised equipment is installed</li>
            <li>Run engine(s) and check gauges</li>
            <li>Test all lights and switches</li>
            <li>Photograph everything for records</li>
            <li>Get owner's manuals for boat and all systems</li>
            <li>Get warranty documentation</li>
            <li>Note any issues in writing before signing</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="warning-box">
            <p><strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Important:</strong> Never sign delivery acceptance paperwork if anything is wrong. Once you sign, fixing problems becomes your responsibility. Note all issues and get commitment for repairs in writing first.</p>
        </div>

        <h3><span class="section-number">8</span>First 30 Days</h3>

        <p>During your first month of ownership:</p>
        <ul class="standard-list">
            <li>Take multiple short trips to familiarize yourself with the boat</li>
            <li>Test all systems in real-world conditions</li>
            <li>Document any warranty issues immediately</li>
            <li>Schedule any needed training or orientation with dealer</li>
            <li>Join owner groups or forums for your boat model</li>
            <li>Create maintenance log and begin documentation</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="page-footer">
            The Boat Pro Newsletter | support@theboatpro.com | Page 16
        </div>
